<p><b>TILLING THE EARTH, CARING FOR THE POOR:
MUSINGS ON STEWARDSHIP AND SUSTAINABILITY</b>.
On Thursday, April 7, 2016, at 7:00pm in Pigott
Auditorium, Seattle University, you’re invited to a
lecture by Jose Ramon Villarin, S.J. President of
Ateneo de Manila University in the Philippines. The
lecture will be followed by a panel discussion with
Patty Bowman, Director of Social Outreach at St.
James Cathedral and Jessie Dye Program and Outreach
Director of Earth Ministry. Drawing insight from Pope
Francis’ encyclical <i>Laudato Si'</i>, panel speakers will
explore the tangible ways local communities have
worked to address issues of ecological injustice.
<i>Information</i>, Institute of Catholic Thought and Culture,
<a href="mailto:ictc@seattleu.edu?subject=Tilling the Earth, Caring for the Poor">ictc@seattleu.edu</a>.</p>
